# Copy to `.env` for local payment testing when the public course-by-slug API returns no row.
# Checkout sends `courseSlug` to the API; the server resolves it the same way as GET /course/slug (including COURSE_ID_BY_SLUG on the backend).
# If you only have a slug (e.g. integrated-mentorship-2028), set UPSC-Backend PAYMENT_FALLBACK_COURSE_OBJECT_ID to a real course _id so initiate-course-payment succeeds without VITE_IMP_*_COURSE_ID.
# These VITE_* ids are optional if slug resolution works end-to-end.
# Use the same MongoDB ObjectId as in your `courses` collection (24 hex chars).

# Optional: one id for any course checkout (last resort)
# VITE_PAYMENT_FALLBACK_COURSE_ID=

# IMP landing pages (match slug)
# VITE_IMP_2027_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_IMP_2028_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_IMP_2029_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_IMP_2030_COURSE_ID=

# UPPCS 2026 landing (/uppcs-mentorship) — slugs: uppcs-2026-complete, uppcs-2026-prelims-booster, uppcs-2026-upsc-combo, uppcs-2026-mains-booster
# Optional: one Mongo _id used for all UPPCS checkouts if you map via UPSC-Backend UPPCS_PAYMENT_FALLBACK_COURSE_OBJECT_ID
# VITE_UPPCS_PAYMENT_COURSE_ID=
# Or per-slug (overrides shared id for that slug):
# VITE_UPPCS_2026_COMPLETE_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_UPPCS_2026_PRELIMS_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_UPPCS_2026_COMBO_COURSE_ID=
# VITE_UPPCS_2026_MAINS_COURSE_ID=
